parts.text: El Clasico: A Fierce Rivalry in Football

* **El Clasico** is the name given to the football match between FC Barcelona and Real Madrid, two of the most successful and well-known clubs in the world.
* The rivalry between the two clubs is one of the most intense in world football, and matches between them are often fiercely contested.
* The name "El Clasico" is derived from the Spanish word for "classic", and is used to reflect the importance and significance of the match.
* The first El Clasico match was played on 13 May 1902, with Barcelona winning 3-1.
* The two teams have met 248 times in all competitions, with Real Madrid winning 101 matches, Barcelona winning 95 matches, and 52 matches ending in a draw.
* In La Liga, the two teams have met 185 times, with Real Madrid winning 76 matches, Barcelona winning 72 matches, and 37 matches ending in a draw.
* The two teams have also met in the Copa del Rey final 11 times, with Barcelona winning 7 matches and Real Madrid winning 4 matches.
* The two teams have met in the UEFA Champions League/European Cup final 5 times, with Real Madrid winning 3 matches and Barcelona winning 2 matches.
* The most recent El Clasico match was played on 16 October 2022, with Real Madrid winning 3-1.
* The next El Clasico match is scheduled to be played on 19 March 2023.
